A list of recommendations to further your career as a scrpiter:

1. Take a course on object oriented programming:

    The first two courses in this specialization focus on object oriented programming in Python.
    https://www.coursera.org/specializations/computer-fundamentals

2. Learn a second language.

    If you're set on becoming a scripter, it would be best for you to learn another object oriented language.
    A language that is perfect for this is Java.
    https://www.coursera.org/courses?languages=en&query=java+

3. Learn more about computer science:

    The final five courses in the specialization mentioned in the first tip will help further your knowledge of CS

4. Get in on a free and open-source project! Ask questions, raise your hand, participate, get your hands dirty...

    https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_free_and_open-source_software_packages


Note: This is just for memory purposes. I don't necessarily plan on doing these steps, but if I decide to go in this direction,
This is a good jumping off point.